1. `j₂' : 𝓞^ →ₐ[ℤ] ℚ ⊗ 𝓞^`, which is the inclusion into the tensor product (i.e., `x ↦ 1 ⊗ x`),
2. An isomorphism `(Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ℤ ℤ ℚ 𝓞 ZHat).symm : ℚ ⊗ 𝓞^ ≃ₐ[ℤ] D ⊗ ZHat`, which reassociates the tensor products (using associativity of tensor products).

